configure
$ git config --global user.name "your name"
$ git config --global user.email yourname@your.domain


initialise
$ mkdir yourrepo
$ cd yourrepo

$ git init
$ git remote add origin git@github.com:yourgithubname/yourgithubreponame.git


add files

$ touch README
$ git add README



commit/push/pull/update repo
first pull other peoples commits to your local copy

$ git pull origin master


then you can push your commits back to master

$ git commit -m 'first commit'
$ git push origin master



get readonly clone of existing repo

$ git clone git://github.com/osde8info/UMLet.git


Note : you CANNOT commit back from this type of clone

get readwrite clone of existing repo

$ git clone  git@github.com:osde8info/UMLet.git


Note : now your git pushes should work !

tag repo

$ git tag 9.9
$ git push --tags
